<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB06464</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT ESTABLISHING SPECIALTY HEALTH CARE UNITS (SHCUs) ATTACHED TO EXISTING REGIONAL HOSPITALS OF THE DEPARTMENT OF HEALTH, AND APPROPRIATING FUNDS THEREFOR</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SHORT TITLE : Intends To Address The Problem Of Specialty Hospitals Being Operationally But Geographically Situated In Metro Manila, Rendering Majority Of Filipinos The Lack Of Access To Health Care; And An Additional Burden For Transportation And Accommodation Expenses For Those Who Can Avail The Services Of These Manila-based Hospitals.
Aims To Bridge The Existing Huge Disparity Of Accessibility To Specific Health Care Services To Address The Medical Needs Of Patients With Diseases Of A Particular Organ Or Group Of Organs, And The Health Care Need By A Particular Group, Such As Children, Women, Or The Elderly.
Proposes For A Ten (10) Year Specialty Health Care Units Development Plan That Will Identify The Establishment Of Shcus Attached To Existing Doh-regional Hospitals.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>GARIN, JANETTE L.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2020-03-03</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON HEALTH ON 2020-03-09</td></tr></table>